{"version": 2, "width": 100, "height": 30, "timestamp": 1764950500, "env": {"SHELL": "/bin/bash", "TERM": "xterm-256color"}, "title": "Adopt HELIX in a new project"}
[0.0, "o", "\r\n\u001b[2m# Day one. You point Claude or Codex at an existing repo. No HELIX yet. The agent has no idea what the project cares about.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.0, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;32m$ ddx install helix\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.4, "o", "Installing HELIX skill into ~/.claude/skills/...\r\n\u2713 skill: helix\r\n\u2713 artifact templates: 32 types under helix/workflows/\r\n"]
[1.5, "o", "\r\n\u001b[2m# The skill lands. No CLI to learn. The agent now knows the artifact catalog.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.0, "o", "\r\n\u001b[36m> /helix what do I have?\u001b[0m\r\n"]
